To call it a wave or anything similarly short-lived is to undermine it. Watching the Gqom Wave documentary, a seeming accompaniment to DJ Maphorisa’s Gqom Wave compilation, one can’t help but notice the faddish excitement that seems to accompany the local, inevitable crossover journey that gqom must take as it moves from a CNN of the RDP townships to a global dance phenomenon. In the South African mainstream, it is nothing short of a biblical moment.
 
